how do you cure your husbands snoring i mean shaking the room snoring i have a couple questions for you does your husband snore evey night and does he fall asleep really fast if so it sounds like he is suffering from sleep apnea here is how sleep apnea occurs the patient predisposed to obstructive sleep apnea has a small pharyngeal airway during sleep the pharyngeal muscles relax allowing the airway to close lack of airflow results in repeated apneic episodes which means the patient wakes up to as many as four hundred times a night and the patient gets absolutly no sleep and there for is constinly tierd and can fall asleep at will i would suggest you have him do a sleep lab at your local hospital what they will do is fit him for a mask and then wire him up and watch him sleep if he is suffering from apnea they will wake him and turn the air on to the mask and then moniter his sleep again when i say air i mean just that it is air not oxygen if you have any questions please feel free to call me at i am doctor mark take care and good luck Sleep apnea Urinary incontinence Insomnia Apnea Sleep disorder Sleep Mechanical ventilation Snoring Narcolepsy Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Drowning Asthma Chronic fatigue syndrome Cluster headache Equine conformation Hypoglycemia Diazepam Out-of-body experience Lung Traumatic brain injury Myocardial infarction Obesity Dream 2005 trial of Michael Jackson The Shining (film) Prostate cancer Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Stomach cancer Euthanasia Jam (TV series) Hypnosis Stroke Lung cancer Hurricane Katrina disaster relief Sleeping Murder Bipolar disorder Psychiatric hospital Pneumonia The Amazing Race Nasal congestion Clinical depression Milton H. Erickson Dialysis Pneumothorax Myasthenia gravis Emergency department Medical cannabis Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) The Empty Child Polycystic ovary syndrome Doctor Who (Enemy Within) Hypertension Down syndrome Night terror Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Sin City Oh My Goddess!